Global Power MOSFET Device Market Insights
Power MOSFET Device Market size was valued at USD 9.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 16.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.9% from 2024 to 2030.

Power MOSFET Device Market Overview
The global Power MOSFET device market was valued at USD 10.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 8.5% during the forecast period, reaching USD 17.9 billion by 2032. The increasing demand for energy-efficient power management systems across various sectors, including automotive, telecommunications, and consumer electronics, is driving the growth of the market. Additionally, advancements in semiconductor technology, such as the development of silicon carbide (SiC) and gallium nitride (GaN) MOSFETs, are expected to contribute significantly to the market’s expansion. With the rising trend of electric vehicles (EVs) and renewable energy systems, the market is poised for further growth. These factors combined indicate a strong, long-term market trajectory for Power MOSFET devices globally.

